Three herons were seen and heard flying south to north on migration in an urban setting. In the field one of the calls sounded drier and raspier. Upon closer inspection of the recording, obtained via a "nocmig" sound-trap that night, it was clear that one of the herons was in fact a Purple Heron; the bird heard calling first in the clip. The sonogram (see full) is also different, with the notes less visible, in comparison to grey.
